  </p>
  <p>
    This study uses the transect method to study the various tree species.
    The plots are 30m2 and sub-divided into 9 subquadrats (each 10m2).
    For more details visit:
    <a href="http://lets-study.ch/" target="_blank">LETS Study</a>
  </p>
  <p>
    To measure species Distribution there are a variety of methods --
    depending on size, and intent of the study.  This study uses <thead>
    transect methodology to study species at different altitudes over
    time.
    <br>
    Transects study organisms over a line (in many cases only a few meters,
    when studying a transition area).  In our case, the transect is many
    kilometers, from the valley floor to the mountain top.  Along this
    line we have study plots.
