  <h4>Other Species Sampling Techniques</h4>
  <p>
    For completeness it can be helpful to know of other species sampling
    techniques -- useful in many other species studies.  In fact, transect
    studies are probably not the most common approach to species studies.
  </p>
  <p>
    Depending on the Environment there are a variety of ways to collect
    species data (other than transect plots and counting individual trees).
    In some cases, like studying mosses - the percent of the plot area is
    used.  In other cases, especially smaller areas where a detailed
    environmental study will be done - random plots are used to study
    a single environment (such as a field or river bed).
